Automated Change Impact Tracker in Foundry that monitors if any dataset changed in pipeline, analyzes downstream dependencies , and uses AIP to generate human-readable impact summaries, classify risk levels, and recommend next actions.
Next Steps
1.	Dataset Change Detection - Monitor for changes in datasets (schema, data volume, freshness, etc.).
2.	Lineage & Dependency Analysis - Identify downstream dependencies of changed datasets
3.	Impact Summary Generation
4.	Risk Classification
5.	Workshop Dashboard Visualization
6.	Automation & Scheduling

Aim:
•	Automated dataset monitoring system that tracks changes in Foundry datasets
•	Change detection capabilities: Row count changes, schema modifications, new datasets
•	Impact analysis: Shows which downstream datasets are affected by changes
•	Audit trail: Stores historical snapshots for comparison and compliance
Technical Implementation
•	Function-based monitoring using TypeScript in Foundry Code Repositories
•	Action Type integration for executing change detection workflows
•	Ontology objects (ChangeSnapshot) to store monitoring data persistently
•	Automated comparison logic between current and previous dataset states
Business Value
•	Proactive change detection - Know immediately when critical datasets change
•	Data quality assurance - Catch unexpected schema or data modifications
•	Downstream impact visibility - Understand ripple effects of data changes
•	Compliance support - Maintain audit trail of all dataset modifications












